          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "LINAC"
                ],
                "institute": "1USAANL"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Studied precursors were were produced",
                "at the Californium Rare Isotope Breeder Upgrade",
                " (CARIBU) facility from the spontaneous fission of a",
                "approx. 100-mCi 252Cf source.The fission products",
                "thermalized in helium buffer gas and extracted from",
                "the exit nozzle of the gas catcher. Ions were then",
                "focused into the RFQ section and accelerated to 36 keV."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Ions of interest were studied using the Beta-decay Paul",
                "Trap (BPT), an open-geometry linear radio frequency",
                "quadrupole (RFQ) ion trap designed for precision",
                "beta-decay studies. BPT was used to collect and suspend",
                "radioactive ions of interest at the center of detector",
                "array. The detector array consisted of"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "SCIN",
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two plastic scintillation telescopes",
                " with EJ-204 plastic scintillators were used to detect",
                " beta particles. dE detector has diameter of 10.6mm and",
                " 1 mm thickness. E detector was 10.2cm thick with 13.3",
                " cm diameter."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MCPLT"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two microchannel plate detectors with nominal",
                " active area of 50.3 x 50.3 mm2 with 1 ns timing",
                " resolution to detect recoiling daughter ions. Position",
                " of ion impact was determined from relative amounts of",
                " charge collected at the corners of resistive anode",
                " with sub-mm precision."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two high-purity germanium p-type HPGe detectors,",
                "  with relative efficiency of 140 and 80% were used",
                "  to detect gamma rays"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Ions of interest were produced by spontaneous fission",
                "of 252Cf, captured by the BPT ion trap and their decay",
                "radiation detected by an array of various radiation",
                "detectors"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
